de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.core

Class LexicalEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.core.LexicalEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IHasID, java.lang.Comparable<LexicalEntry>

    public class LexicalEntry
extends java.lang.Object
implements IHasID, java.lang.Comparable<LexicalEntry>
    LexicalEntry is a class representing a lexeme in a given language. The LexicalEntry is a container for managing the RelatedForm, WordForm and Sense classes. Therefore, the LexicalEntry manages the relationship between the forms and their related senses.

    A LexicalEntry instance can have from zero to many different senses.

    Author:
    Zijad Maksuti
    See Also:
    RelatedForm, WordForm
